semantic_units: The green soda bottle with the green cap is used for freshness indication. When carbonated beverage loses pressure, the pressure regulator inside the canister tries to equilibrium the pressure by opening the valve. The equilibrium can be achieved by reducing the volume of the canister. When the pressure inside the canister is not equalized, the pressure indication on the outside of the canister will show amber or red color to warn the user. If the pressure remains amber or red for a long time, the user should mix the soda and drink it soon or else the sodium chloride will precipitate and cause metal poisoning.  The reason why the green soda bottle shows good pressure indication is because of the green bottle is a newly purchased green soda bottle will show dark green color if not refilled for a long time. If the soda is refilled in a green bottle that shows dark green color, the color of the soda will not change for a while and the user will think the soda is good to drink. But if the newly purchased green soda bottle is used to refill the pressurized green soft drink, the pressure will show good indication on the outside of the canister and the user will not drink it right away.

In this example, the white hutch is superior because it is made of wood, which in New Zealand is seen as a natural resource that should only be used economically and with care.
